des mail references. It seems the jersey-core packages might incorporate entity providers for mail and JAXB. Existing builds probably include these dependencies from prior generations. If the issue fails, I’ll need an OSGi upgrade, and I wonder if including existing builds in the workflow is necessary. Determining the dependencies carefully is important!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting library dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering that the context is just a starting point and the current library at version 1.9 includes existing tests. I should look into any concrete evidence for the advisory preparation phase. It’s worth inspecting the POM to see if the JSR311 API is provided, but it seems jersey-core already includes javax.ws.rs classes and exports them in the manifest, so that might not be necessary. I'll check if the jar actually contains javax/ws/rs classes to verify everything.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Wn14v2gLPTGUgz1QdmcfMFLk|fc_041e192a54c7ddd6016a42ecc47bd481948d479990d47078fc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nfor v in ['1.14']:\n    data=urllib.request.urlopen(f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/sun/jersey/jersey-core/{v}/jersey-core-{v}.jar').read()\n    z=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(data))\n    for cls in ['javax/ws/rs/core/Response.class','javax/mail/internet/MimeMultipart.class','javax/xml/bind/JAXBContext.class','org/osgi/framework/BundleReference.class']:\n        print(v, cls, cls in z.namelist())\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4954, "output": 1159, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29665, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782770865056, "responseId": "resp_041e192a54c7ddd6016a42ecb2e1548194858a826d070cb423"}}
